因可能与TiDB的存储层交互有关，验证了假设中关于TiDB存储层的担忧。\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_trace_keys\": [\"rrt_max\", \"frontend->productcatalogservice\", \"productcatalogservice->tidb\", \"error_ratio\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"productcatalogservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Response time for GetProduct increased from normal 9209.96 ms to anomaly 12459.20 ms.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"productcatalogservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"error_ratio\",\n      \"evidence\": \"PD server timeout errors occurring frequently.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n此分析支持假设，即这个异常可能与TiDB存储层交互相关，由多个因素及组件的表现所证实。", "log_analysis_findings": "Based on the retrieved logs for the specified time period, I have performed an analysis to verify the hypothesis regarding the TiDB storage layer. Here's a summary:\n\n### Key Findings from Log Analysis:\n1. The logs indicate multiple instances of `PD server timeout` errors, primarily affecting the `frontend` and `productcatalogservice`. These errors suggest issues in interaction between these services and the TiDB storage components.\n2. Error messages frequently reference the code `Error 9001 (HY000): PD server timeout` which implicates delays or failures in the TiDB-PD server cluster, crucial for transaction processing.\n3. The problem seems to be consistent with what was hypothesized: delays and issues in the TiDB storage layer are manifesting in higher-level services (as pointed by both logs and external evidence from Trace and Metric experts).\n\n### Identified Log Keywords:\n- `PD server timeout`\n- `rpc error`\n- `Error 9001 (HY000)`\n\n### Conclusion:\nThe analysis of the logs strongly supports the hypothesis that the root cause of the observed anomalies is due to issues in the TiDB storage layer, particularly interactions with the PD server.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_log_keys\": [\"PD server timeout\", \"rpc error\", \"Error 9001 (HY000)\"],\n 